[1] Cholera - Mozambique (Cabo Delgado province)
Date: Sat 4 Apr 2015
Source: AllAfrica, Mozambique News Agency (AIM) [edited]
http://allafrica.com/stories/201504060261.html


Cholera has spread to the northern Mozambican province of Cabo Delgado, according to the Provincial Director of Health. Saozinha Agostinho, cited in Saturday's [4 Apr 2015] issue of the Maputo daily "Noticias". Cabo Delgado becomes the 6th province to be struck by the disease since December 2014. The others are Niassa, Nampula, Tete, Zambezia, and Sofala.

Agostinho announced that 38 cases of cholera have been diagnosed in the provincial capital, Pemba. Cases of severe diarrhea, particularly in the neighborhood of Cariaco, began to be notified a week ago. Laboratory analysis showed that the great majority of the victims were indeed suffering from cholera.

A cholera treatment center has now been reactivated in the Eduardo Mondlane neighborhood, and all people entering the Provincial Hospital in Pemba with symptoms of cholera are redirected to the center. So far no deaths from cholera have been reported in Pemba.

The latest report from the Health Minister, issued on Monday [30 Mar 2015] before cholera was confirmed in Cabo Delgado, was that since the beginning 2015, there have been 7408 cases, of whom 55 have died, which is a lethality rate of 0.7 per cent.

--
