[The province of Cabo Delgado of Mozambique is located in the extreme northeast of the country and can be found on a map of the country at http://www.ezilon.com/maps/images/africa/Mozambique-physical-map.gif. A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3292841,177. - Mod.LL]

******
[2] Cholera - India (Odisha State)
Date: Thu 2 Apr 2015
Source: New Indian Express [edited]
http://www.newindianexpress.com/states/odisha/Cholera-Detected-in-Mahakalpada/2015/04/02/article2742932.ece


Even as the State [Odisha] struggles to contain outbreak of communicable diseases, cholera has been detected in Kendrapara's Mahakalpada block.

With diarrhea reports pouring in from Kumbharpada and Baitisahi, the Health department conducted a house-to-house survey and found 44 cases. Of the 2 samples sent for investigation, 1 tested positive for _Vibrio cholerae_.

The emergence of cholera in the block is attributed to leakage in the water supply pipeline. The district administration has gone on war-footing to repair the pipelines apart from providing drinking water to locals through tankers.

--
